 class. The book also gives an engrossing account of how and why Anna became an icon of American culture in The King and I and its many adaptations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aBritishxBiographyxThailand. 0aBritishzThailandvBiography. 0aGovernessesxBiographyxThailand. 0aGovernesseszThailandvBiography. 0aRacially mixed peoplexBiographyxIndia. 0aRacially mixed peoplezIndiavBiography. 0aWomen authorsvBiography. 0aWomen authorsxBiography. 0aWomen journalistsvBiography. 0aWomen journalistsxBiography. 0aWomen travelersvBiography. 0aWomen travelersxBiography. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh  a19th century.  aacademic.  aanna leonowens.  aarmy brat.  aasia.  aasian history.  abiographical.  abiography.  abritish colonies.  acolonial.  acolonialism.  acolonizers.  agoverness.  aharem.  aindia.  ajournalism.  ajournalist.  aking of siam.  alife story.  amilitary family.  amilitary.  amixed race.  amusical theatre.  amusicals.  apop culture.  areal life.  aresearch.  arevolution.  aroyalty.  ascholarly.  asiam.  astrong women.  ateacher.  athe king and i.  atravel writer.  atrue story.  auntold story.  avictorian literature.  avictorian.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093399640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520933996423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520933996/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles